-- 
Cameroon Cocoa Exports at $2.98 a Kilogram in Week to July 25

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-07-26T17:31:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/cameroon-cocoa-exports-at-2-98-a-kilogram-in-week-to-july-25.html
The export price of cocoa from
Cameroon,  Africa ’s fourth-biggest grower of the beans, was
little changed in the week to July 25, according to data from
the Cocoa and Coffee Board.  The average rate declined to 1,350 CFA francs ($2.98) a
kilogram (2.2 pounds), compared with 1,352 CFA francs a week
earlier, according to Bloomberg calculations of data sent by
mobile-phone text message from the board today.  Cameroon’s  cocoa production in the season, which started in
August, to May 31 rose 23 percent to 222,200 metric tons,
according to the Douala-based board’s data. Cameroon follows
 Ivory Coast , Ghana and Nigeria in African cocoa output. The
season ends July 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 